column3: “Super dense buds, often with some purple/grey/blue coloration, thick stems and opaque, white trichomes. Smell is classic indica - earthy and dank with an animalic note, yet there's a strong sweet/minty/spicy aspect that seems to really carry. The vapor from this one is thick, sweet and permeating. Overall, very pleasant aroma though problematic if you're trying to keep the smell down. The buzz is fairly long-lasting ...”

“This is some crystal covered, purple-tinted bud. The dispensary sells it as a pure indica. It has a sweet, grape-dominant flavor profile. While I consider myself a sativa-guy, I certainly appreciate a good indica for before bed or to have while kicking back with some friends. This is a strain that has a bit of a delay when it hits you, but when it does, it hits you hard. Your body slowly goes numb and at first it see...”
“This shit would get Willie Nelson stoned.”
“A dreamy, happy head change that left my body stranded on the couch watching king fu movies for a while.”

“Oh dear, where to begin. This strain I acquired first in Arizona @ AZ Natural Selections (Excellent Dispensary BTW). purchased an oil cartridge. It was a distinct kind of earthy and a little pine. At first it was a mediocre kind of high. I proceeded to indulge in a little more. I feel honky dory. So I looked at the profile for it. Then. It creeped up on me. Suddenly I was confused and extremely euphoric and mellow. R...”
“Smells fucking good”

“Great indica without too many paranoid effects, which I'm prone to with indicas. I have muscle pain, deep vein pain, stomach issues and chronic nausea as well as anxiety and depression. This helped with all of these! It does take about 5 minutes to feel any sort of medication, but it lasts hours. My pain was almost gone and I could finally eat something after 2 days. Will be coming back to this one again.”

“This is definitely not for beginner smokers, when i was in 7th grade i had homegrown cataract kush and me and my friends smoked it and it legit felt like Trevors rage" mode in GTA 5 my vision was fucked up bad like everything had a higher contrast
column4: at the same time i kept on "falling asleep" then waking backup while standing up and i had cotton mouth
column5: although it was a bad experience i really liked this strain but t...”"

column3: “This was recommended to me at a dispensary outside Denver (The Highway in Downieville, CO) when I told the bud tender I wanted something Indica dominant that would relax me at night, make me happy, make me feel like my body's getting buzzed for once. I have quite a tolerance and it's been a while since I actually felt high. She suggested this hybrid instead of pure indica.  She was right. I'm high again with a good b...”

“this the second time i have tried cataract kush  the effect have a much different  quailtys this time more sativa feeling with ups and downs how ever this mud was much less dry more triclyomes on the bud to provide a more cerebral high great calm effects for anxiety”

“Cataract Kush is one of the most iconic strong earthy strains that is a favorite amongst the rest of my other patients here.
The Smell: Popping open the funky swirly label in purple I am hit in the face with a pungent odors of funky then fresh cut grass and earthy fresh mud as if it has just rained, very loud.
Bud Freshness: I can always tell how well a bud has been treated when it comes to not only how it smells but...”

“I am just back from NYC after a Cancer Treatments in Rochester NY at my favourite clinic with RF 
Chronic Pain Treatments.   We again received a wonderful Care Package from NYC's first and largest Medical Cannabis Dispensary.

I cannot hold back gushing about Cataract Kush my first try of this Pure East meets West Indica a cross of LA's Indica Super Strain O G Kush and DNA Genetics LA Confidential to issue. Hard Pain...”

“Smoked this beautiful tree post workout for muscle soreness and my god! Pain and stress on my muscles was lifted as I became lifted. The high was strong coming on in small spurts and before I knew it I was completely relaxed! It's a creeper but one of the best highs I have ever experienced!”
“Excellent for a mellow pain free high. Great for sleepys.”

“Very dense crystally buds, you get a bunch of Kief off the buds when using a grinder, euphoric high, great for pain, high lasts a long time, also a creeper high that keeps building up and up after you're done smoking”

“This is one hell of a strain! Its high THC and high CBD levels make it pack a real, long lasting punch. Though it says hybrid, this is a heavy indica leaning strain. This strain has given me the most intense euphoria I've ever felt from weed, and I'm no novice smoker.
Being that its an indica, it knocks away all my pain. It also has a habit of initiating couch locks. Its a wonderful bed time strain, in my opinion.”

“I picked up some of this bud from my favorite delivery service and it sure does not disappoint!  Super frosty dense nugs and almost a charcoal color.   Very smooth  smoke and a creeper high!  I would recommend giving this strain a full 20 minutes to take effect.  Smoke a little too much and it's nap time.  

JediForce”

“If you're sore have heavy pain and cramps then I suggest cataract Kush. Cataract Kush is great if you have a hard time just moving throughout the day but say you go on a walk and you want to go further  before your joints are hurting cataract Kush is able to take away the pain and leave you manageable. It's a very dark earthy strain and it's very dank if grown correctly. Hey causes a lot of dry eyes and dry mouth but...”

“This is my go to for night time.  It quashes the pain in my colon and lets me sleep through the night.  If you smoke during the day you will have couch lock so save it for when you don't have to go out.”

“I found this  strain to be amazing! The high honesty builds up more an more after you smoke an comes down with a nice chill high. Helped me build up an appetite also helped with nausea and my lack of ability to sleep.”

“Very dense crystally buds, you get a bunch of Kief off the buds when using a grinder, euphoric high, great for pain, high lasts a long time, also a creeper high that keeps building up and up after you're done smoking”
“currently my favorite. tastes good, gives you a nice calm high, a little giggly but not too bad. helps with my headaches.”

“This is a heavy stone that creeps up about ten minutes after smoking and keeps building in intensity long after the smoking has ended. Combine that with the creeper effect, and it can cause serious couchlock for uninitiated. Lightweight smokers may have an unpleasant experience if unprepared, but those who are after the big stone indica will be pleased with the hashy, spicy-sweet flavor that brings the rich pungency ...”

“Like some of the others have said, this strain is not for lightweights. A little goes a long way, but if you can handle the stronger THC content, this is a nice strain. For me, the high peaks about 45 minutes after two or three decent rips from my bong, and I feel relaxed and quite happy. Kind of a harsh inhale, but it has a nice pine exhale. It's versatile enough where I can either sleep or go about my day doing sch...”
“A decent high. I was in some minor pain from practice this past week and rolled up this beauty and quickly felt relief. Kind of a sluggish and intense high so be mindful of when you medicate.”

“fantastic all-around strain for relaxation and pain relief. I tried this strain in concentrate form and it really brings out the harshness a bit, but otherwise a clean taste with solid  and well-rounded effects, (though a little on the relaxing side) so I would even recommend for afternoon or evening :)”
“I really enjoyed this stain a lot. The buds are beautiful. They are relatively dense,dark green with a large amount tricombs covering the outside.”
